### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It will handle routing, data reading/writing from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and business logic for all eight pages. Since the application is not very complex, consolidating backend logic into this single file is efficient and maintainable.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web application pages, each corresponding to one of the eight pages specified in the requirements. These templates will use a Python web framework templating engine (e.g., Flask’s Jinja2) to dynamically render data.

  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard page layout and elements.
  - `property_search.html` — Property search page with filters and property grid.
  - `property_details.html` — Detailed view of a selected property.
  - `property_inquiry.html` — Form page for submitting property inquiries.
  - `my_inquiries.html` — Page listing all user inquiries with status and management.
  - `my_favorites.html` — Page showing favorite properties with management options.
  - `agent_directory.html` — Directory listing real estate agents with search.
  - `locations.html` — Page displaying featured locations with sorting and navigation.

- **static/**  
  Folder for static assets such as CSS, JavaScript, and images.

  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across all pages.
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
  - `images/` — Folder to store any property or agent images if applicable (optional as per requirements).

- **data/**  
  Directory containing all local text files used for data storage as per the specified formats:

  - `properties.txt` — Property listings data.
  - `locations.txt` — Locations data.
  - `inquiries.txt` — Property inquiries data.
  - `favorites.txt` — Favorite properties data.
  - `agents.txt` — Real estate agents data.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, frontend templates, static resources, and data storage, aligning well with the project requirements and ensuring maintainability and scalability."

